    "updated_at": "2013-08-13T13:44:41Z",
    "body": "You don't have to redo the entire API yet. I'll do some tests to see how\nlong it takes to rebuild the menu, maybe it will be fine to do it that way.\n\nOn Tuesday, August 13, 2013, Cheng Zhao wrote:\n\n> Your request means:\n> 1. The menu item's state and attributes should be able to be changed\n> dynamically without recreating the whole menu.\n> 2. Provide a way in Menu.buildFromTemplate API to add custom fields to\n> menu items.\n> \n> is it right?\n> \n> The menu API was implemented by reusing Chromium's ui library, which is\n> designed for static menus, e.g. there is now way to change menu items\n> without recreating the whole menu with this library. I'll get rid of\n> Chromium's menu library and write the menu API from scratch.\n> \n> —\n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHubhttps://github.com/atom/atom-shell/issues/54#issuecomment-22547144\n> .\n"
