    "created_at": "2013-08-13T16:44:48Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-08-13T16:44:48Z",
    "body": "For now I just want to be able to enable/disable menu items, I don't need to be able to add/remove them. I've got this currently working in Atom's `cj-application-menus` branch. But instead of using an extra `metadata` attribute on the menu item i'm hacking the `groupId` attribute to store if an item should be disabled when all windows are closed.\n\nWould you have to rewrite the entire menu API if we just wanted to attach some extra data to a menu item?\n"
